Every hour on the hour. A woman's story of pain. Even if men didn't WANT to listen  men would be bombarded on their TLs w/ narrative.
But if you take a look at the dominant narrative on Twitter  it's a story of women's hurt and abuse. Every day. Every single day.
For one thing  the incorrect assumption that IF BM say what they go through means they're saying "me too" as a means of deflection...
Then you got Brothers like this...let me tell you why this doesn't hold up... https://t.co/Zb7hTwh0Me
It's not like we believe it anyway.
Plus  who are we kidding? 85% are going to marry BW and spend the rest of our lives w/ them  so calling them trash is just grandstanding.
...according to their logic  we'd be within our rights to call them "trash". But no thanks  that type of thinking is unhelpful.
If u measured my and many other BMs experiences w/ BW next to that of some BW...
Simply bc it's an unintelligent thing to do. It's imbecilic. And yes  it's unfair.
Still  all that said  I could never see myself telling a BW she's responsible for what other BW have done to me  my brothers  my homies  etc
And before anyone comes in these mentions asserting the the hurt BW and BM face are apples and oranges---don't.
Then  from a birds eye view  there's that "villain vs victim" appearance. Us on the ground know what's up of course  but you know...
...and meanwhile continue (collectively) performing the abuses against them  it can appear that way.
The truth is  BW are human just like us. They never were more moral than us. Ever. But when we don't speak on it in real time...
BM and BW relations are much more manageable bc then  there can't be that "well then why didn't you say anything before" dodge.
Now of course I'm not advocating airing out your dirty laundry on twitter  simply bc that's high school...
Then suddenly you're tired of it and you give her that infamous speech and go down the laundry list of offenses you been letting slide.
It's kind of like when you're in a relationship and your girl brings up every thing you do that pesters her  offends her  etc  in real time.
I assure you  it's not.
Bc BM are taught to hold these things in  it appears that the abuse is one sided.
Plus  bringing that up in RESPONSE to the Twitter propagated narrative that BM hate BW appears disingenuous  even if it's not.
This BM vs BW "war" relies on BM choosing not to voice the same hurt they've experienced at the hands of BW  so it looks uneven.
